00:23:04.440 --> 00:23:08.060
you then co-register the tissue, and you know where those barcodes are with respect

413
00:23:08.070 --> 00:23:09.000
to where your tissue was.

414
00:23:10.480 --> 00:23:10.900
However,

415
00:23:11.720 --> 00:23:14.460
the cells themselves are bigger than the individual barcodes.

416
00:23:16.120 --> 00:23:20.080
And so how do you then ascribe these individual barcode squares that are about

