427
00:23:51.960 --> 00:23:54.480
But then again, you're losing a lot of information when you do that.

428
00:23:54.500 --> 00:23:56.980
But again, what's the lesser of two evils?

429
00:23:57.740 --> 00:24:00.230
So something to consider. If you're doing some of these type of approaches, you're

430
00:24:00.260 --> 00:24:03.920
doing these sequencing-based approaches, how do you know which

431
00:24:03.960 --> 00:24:06.570
barcodes to ascribe when you co-register your tissue?

432
00:24:07.140 --> 00:24:09.480
Something to consider, and I think this approach is actually a really good

